  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n0.2.0\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAnvil seemingly allows for the execution of invalid transactions. I'm able to create an invalid transaction, by having a signature on a transaction where the `s` value is greater than `n/2` these transaction should be invalid https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-2.md#specification, so even though the signature recovers to the correct / address and public key it shouldn't be able to execute. Here's the decoded version of the signed transaction -- https://rawtxdecode.in/?rawTx=0x02f873827a6980849184e72a849184e72a82753094b89ff4e9ad6b33f69153fa710f9849f51712eec4872386f26fc1000080c080a02b3416d8559c481663227484c8f7dea8705b6e1109d67bb3d0d760ef3b271503a0ec9ca501276589e81c0381db75e978cba19497bc0c15670df49c3a9ef411d70c.\r\n\r\nand also a gist of how I was executing the transaction -- https://gist.github.com/k-xo/670520238fbb1c1b950b3bf10211f6be\r\n\r\nand some of the anvil and script logs\r\n<img width=\"746\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-20 at 17 57 49\" src=\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/32230412/0118d5cf-9cf2-4986-b5ea-9c6f6e9b0d3a\">\r\n<img width=\"529\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-20 at 17 56 59\" src=\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/32230412/6cd650ad-fb12-421b-9757-3d1e0c62e165\">\r\n\r\n",
